article.headline: Stetson 63, Flagler 51
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- Junior transfer Karl Hollingsworth scored a career-high 17 points to lead Stetson past Flagler 63-51 Friday night. Anthony Register added 15 points and E.J. Gordon had 13 points and nine rebounds for Stetson (1-0). Hollingsworth, a 6-foot-5, 230-pound transfer from Tulane, tallied 10 points in the second half of his Stetson debut. Flagler (3-2) was led by Robbie Reyes with 12 points and eight rebounds, Bryan Borstelmann with 11 points and nine rebounds and Darrell Freeman with 11 points and eight rebounds. Flagler led 34-33 with under 17 minutes to play before Hollingsworth hit back-to-back jumpers to put the Hatters ahead 37-34. The Saints stayed close until a 10-0 Stetson run with 7:20 to play. Hollingsworth connected on back-to-back baskets in the paint to give Stetson its first double-digit lead at 54-43 with 5:25 left. Register converted three of five free throws over the next 1:38 to give Stetson a 58-43 lead, it's largest of the game. Flagler was 17 of 66 from the field, for 25.8 percent.
